    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n<details><summary>Final goal</summary>\n\nTo avoid an [XYProblem](https://xyproblem.info/), I'll start by saying my final goal:\nI want something like `vim.lsp.buf.definition`, with some changes.\n\n1. I want to it to open in a new tab and switch to it...\n2. ...unless the file is already open in a tab, in which case I just want to switch to that tab.\n\nI am trying to use `vim.lsp.ListOps.on_list`, but am running into the issue I'll describe now\n</details>\n\n\nIn Lua, I am trying to open a new tab, create a window in that tab, and set the buffer for that window.  However, I am stuck on the first part.  I don't know how to open a new tab in Lua besides for just `tabnew`, but `tabnew` doesn't return the `tabnr`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe C API has `‎win_new_tabpage‎`, which could work.  However, `‎win_new_tabpage‎` isn't available from the Lua API.\n\nWould you accept a patch that adds `‎vim.api.nvim_win_new_tabpage‎`?",
