        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "follow-up: Is there an api to change the current tab to another tab?  My WIP current implementation looks like\n\n```lua\nfunction handleGotoDefinition(options)\n\tlocal title =options.title\n\tlocal all_items = options.items\n\tlocal method = options.context.method\n\tlocal bufnr = options.context.bufnr\n\tlocal result = all_items[1]\n\tlocal result_bufnr = result.bufnr or vim.fn.bufadd(all_items[1].filename)\n\n\tlocal maybeW = vim.fn.win_findbuf(result_bufnr)[1]\n\tprint(maybeW)\n\tif maybeW then\n\t\tlocal w = maybeW\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(w, result_bufnr)\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(w, { result.lnum, result.col - 1 })\n                -- HELP: how do I switch to the tab/split for `w`?\n                -- pseudo-code:\n                -- vim.api.nvim_switch_to_tab(vim.api.nvim_find_tab_containing_window(w))\n\telse\n\t\tvim.cmd('tabnew');\n\t\tvim.bo[result_bufnr].buflisted = true;\n\t\tlocal w = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(w, result_bufnr);\n\n\tend\nend\n\nvim.lsp.buf.definition({on_list = handleGotoDefinition})\n```\n\nAs you can see on the line `-- HELP`, I don't know how to switch to the tab where `w` is currently open in.\n\n\nEDIT: nvm @seandewar helped me.  I needed `vim.api.nvim_set_current_win(w)`",
